    "Her days can't be over, dreams spilling over onto childhood diaries and wistful missives screamed to be let free. "

    "She wants to see her friends again, travel the world, fall in love. She wants, wants, wants but fact refuses to budge to accommodate her."

    "Seized by frenzy, she thrashes about. Her chains don't give. The magic pulsing through them renders her powerless."

    "Fear shoots through her, a lance in her heart. All Astrid can do is stare in disappointment."

