label day_three_cont:

    scene day3_3

    "The rattle of her chain cuts through the eerie choir with a strange, syncopated beat. They walk down a seemingly endless hall, Jun keeping her vision fixed squarely to the floor. "

    scene bghallway

    show astrid evil neutral at topright
    show jun evil neutral at cleft

    "She can see the back of Astrid's shoes, a steady march towards her undoing."

    "It is a rhythm that, much like time, can only keep marching forward. "

    "She does not falter."

    "As Jun drags her feet on the uneven stone, she experiences an inkling of familiarity. "

    "Surveying her surroundings, a memory makes its way back to the forefront of her consciousness."

    "It was this exact passage that connected the town to the rest of the outside world. "

    "She had observed it from afar in the dead of night while snatching reckless humans venturing too far outside the sanctity of their settlement, and she had seen it up close when she was escorted to her place of imprisonment. "

    "Just beyond the passage was the town's High Altar, a hulking megalith carved from the base of the mountain the village sat atop. Lining the edge of the altar itself were runes not dissimilar to the ones carved in her cell, or pressed into the metal of her cuffs. "

    scene day3_4

    "A few inches away from the opening, Astrid stops dead in her tracks and looks her in the eye for the first time since they started their walk."

    scene day3_5

    "Lifting her head while caressing her cheek with her thumb, she coos, softened now that Jun's hysterics had dwindled to a solemn resignation."

    a "...It's alright, Jun. "

    scene day3_6

    a "You don't need to fear it. I'll be there with you. "

    scene day3_7

    "With a tug, Astrid drags her face closer and closer, until they're a hairsbreadth apart. "

    "Their lips press together, and a shock goes through her body. She is helpless to resist. Astrid's touch travels down, down, down. Running careful fingers against her side, squeezing against soft and yielding skin."

    scene day3_8

    "Astrid's touch travels down, down, down. Running careful fingers against her side, squeezing against soft and yielding skin."

    "She had spent her whole life fighting the delusion that love could be anything kind. It was easier to believe violence was the only way to profess devotion, but the sheer care and gentleness of Astrid's callused, battle-worn hands makes her crave more."

    "Her mind is spinning, the choir's song fading away into nothing but noise, giving way for Astrid's voice and her voice alone to move through her ears."

    a "You've had to fight for so long, haven't you?"

    "Why give her this now, when there's no hope? When she'd stopped fighting?"

    "Was this all her life was cracked up to be? Toyed with and at the mercy of another?"

    "If she had given in sooner, would she have found the love she had always wanted?"

    a "You won't have to fight so hard anymore. I'll love you, Jun~"

    "Maybe in death she would reach a serenity she had seldom allowed herself in life."

    "Astrid would be with her for the rest of her time. Astrid would love her for as long as she lived. Astrid believed she could be perfect. "

    "Astrid, Astrid, Astrid-"

